As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 251 people, 83 households, and 52 families residing in the village.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2020: Highland Park village, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Highland+Park+village;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 230 people, 107 households, and 81 families residing in the village.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2010: Highland Park village, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Highland+Park+village;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

===2000 census===
At the 2000 [[census]],<ref name="GR2" /> there were 244 people, 112 households and 73 families residing in the village. The population density was {{convert|544.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 174 housing units at an average density of {{convert|388.1|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the village was 94.26% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.82% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 3.69% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 1.23% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.82% of the population.

In 2000, there were 112 households, of which 18.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 62.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 0.9% had a female householder with no husband present, and 34.8% were non-families. 31.3% of all households were made up of individuals, and 19.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.18 and the average family size was 2.70.

In 2000, 16.8% of the population were under the age of 18, 6.1% from 18 to 24, 18.4% from 25 to 44, 26.2% from 45 to 64, and 32.4% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 51 years. For every 100 females, there were 90.6 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 84.5 males.

In 2000, the [[median household income]] was $41,875 and the median family income was $56,667. Males had a median income of $43,333 vand females $18,750. The [[per capita income]] was $30,097. None of the families and 3.9% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]].

